premise_source_doc_sentence: Indian 100 Crore Club is an unofficial designation by the Indian film trade and the media , related to Indian language films that have net 100 crore  (  1 billion Indian rupees  )  or more in India after deducting the entertainment tax .
3 Idiots is a Indian coming of age comedy-drama .
Four of Khan 's filmsGhajini , 3 Idiots , Dhoom 3 , and PK have held records for being the highest-grossing Bollywood film of all time .

While a number of Indian films had previously crossed 100 crore worldwide , starting with the 1994 Salman Khan starring Bollywood film Hum Aapke Hain Kaun , the 100 Crore Club emerged after the 2008 Aamir Khan starrer Ghajini became the first Indian film to net gross over 100 crore domestically .
The later Aamir Khan films 3 Idiots , Dhoom 3 , PK and Dangal expanded the club to 200 , 300 , 400 , 500 , 600 and 700 crore .
